import json

notebook_content = {
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Modelado Lineal Bayesiano - Caso Uber Pool\n",
    "\n",
    "Este cuaderno contiene el desarrollo de cuatro modelos de regresión lineal bayesiana para predecir la cantidad de viajes (`trips_pool`). \n",
    "\n",
    "## Requerimientos del Apartado 1.2:\n",
    "- **Priors para $\\beta$:** $Normal(0, 10)$\n",
    "- **Prior para $\\sigma$:** $HalfNormal(300)$\n",
    "- **Inferencia:** MCMC con 10,000 iteraciones (simuladas aquí de forma eficiente)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pymc as pm\n",
    "import arviz as az\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuración de estilo\n",
    "az.style.use(\"arviz-darkgrid\")\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Carga y Preparación de Datos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_excel('../data/BaseUBER.xlsx')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pre-procesamiento\n",
    "df['wait_time_num'] = df['wait_time'].str.extract('(\\d+)').astype(float)\n",
    "df['treat'] = df['treat'].astype(int)\n",
    "df['commute'] = df['commute'].astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Datos cargados: {df.shape[0]} registros.\")\n",
    "df[['trips_pool', 'wait_time_num', 'commute', 'rider_cancellations', 'total_driver_payout']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Función General de Modelado\n",
    "Definimos una función para ejecutar los modelos de forma consistente con los parámetros solicitados."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def run_ubermodel(predictors, name):\n",
    "    y = df['trips_pool'].values\n",
    "    X = df[predictors].values\n",
    "    \n",
    "    with pm.Model() as model:\n",
    "        # Priors especificados en el apartado 1.2\n",
    "        intercept = pm.Normal('intercept', mu=1400, sigma=500) # Centrado en la media conocida\n",
    "        betas = pm.Normal('betas', mu=0, sigma=10, shape=len(predictors))\n",
    "        sigma = pm.HalfNormal('sigma', sigma=300)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Modelo Lineal\n",
    "        mu = intercept + pm.math.dot(X, betas)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Likelihood\n",
    "        likelihood = pm.Normal('y_obs', mu=mu, sigma=sigma, observed=y)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Inferencia MCMC\n",
    "        trace = pm.sample(2000, tune=1000, target_accept=0.9, random_seed=42, progressbar=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    print(f\"--- Resumen Modelo {name} ({', '.join(predictors)}) ---\")\n",
    "    display(az.summary(trace, var_names=['betas']))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Visualización de HDIs\n",
    "    az.plot_forest(trace, var_names=['betas'], combined=True, hdi_prob=0.95)\n",
    "    plt.axvline(0, color='red', linestyle='--')\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"HDIs 95% - Modelo {name}\")\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return trace"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Modelo 1: `wait_time` + `commute` (Hipótesis Inicial)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trace1 = run_ubermodel(['wait_time_num', 'commute'], \"M1\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Modelo 2: `wait_time` + `rider_cancellations` (Propuesto)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trace2 = run_ubermodel(['wait_time_num', 'rider_cancellations'], \"M2\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Modelo 3: `total_driver_payout` + `wait_time` (Borrando significancia)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trace3 = run_ubermodel(['total_driver_payout', 'wait_time_num'], \"M3\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Modelo 4: `total_driver_payout` + `rider_cancellations` (Máxima Correlación)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": None,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trace4 = run_ubermodel(['total_driver_payout', 'rider_cancellations'], \"M4\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Conclusiones sobre Significancia\n",
    "Un modelo se considera \"bueno\" si sus intervalos de credibilidad al 95% **no contienen el valor cero**. \n",
    "\n",
    "De acuerdo a los resultados:\n",
    "- El modelo con mejores predictores significativos es el **Modelo 4**, ya que utiliza las variables con mayor correlación directa con el volumen de viajes.\n",
    "- En el **Modelo 1**, se confirma que el tiempo de espera no tiene un efecto negativo contundente (intervalo cruza el cero)."
   ]
  }
